# This file represents the encrypted payload of the .tckpkg package.
#
# In a real package, this is a binary blob produced by:
#   AES-256-GCM(key=HKDF(recipient_key), plaintext=tar(tck-execution.json + assets/))
#
# Contents when decrypted:
#   tck-execution.json          (same as plain/tck-execution.json)
#   assets/
#     schemas/
#       business_partner_certificate.json
#       notification_header.json
#     testdata/
#       request_certificate_body.json
#       sample_certificate.pdf
#
# The Player decrypts this at boot time using the recipient's private key,
# then proceeds with normal asset resolution from the decrypted tar.
#
# Encryption parameters:
#   Algorithm: AES-256-GCM
#   Key derivation: HKDF-SHA256 from age X25519 shared secret
#   Nonce: 12 bytes, unique per encryption
#   AAD: manifest checksum (binds payload to its manifest)
#
# This placeholder contains a hex-encoded representation of what the
# encrypted binary would look like (first 256 bytes shown):

0000: 61 67 65 2d 65 6e 63 72 79 70 74 69 6f 6e 2e 6f  age-encryption.o
0010: 72 67 2f 76 31 0a 2d 3e 20 58 32 35 35 31 39 20  rg/v1.-> X25519 
0020: 71 6c 33 7a 37 68 6a 79 35 34 70 77 33 68 79 77  ql3z7hjy54pw3hyw
0030: 77 35 61 79 79 66 67 37 7a 71 67 76 63 37 77 33  w5ayyfg7zqgvc7w3
0040: 6a 32 65 6c 77 38 7a 6d 72 6a 32 6b 67 35 73 66  j2elw8zmrj2kg5sf
0050: 6e 39 61 71 0a 00 00 00 00 00 00 00 00 00 00 00  n9aq............
0060: [... AES-256-GCM ciphertext of tar archive ...]
